cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.ITP, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with Rate Distortion Function (RDF) and Joint Source-Channel Coding (JSCC), which are core topics in Information Theory. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the application of RDF in the context of multidimensional partially observed Gaussian-Markov source, which is a common model in multimedia signal processing. 
3. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper deals with source coding and channel coding, which are fundamental topics in signal processing. 
4. cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability) - The paper involves the use of probability theory in the analysis of RDF and JSCC. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the concept of nonanticipative RDF, which is related to the idea of causality in machine learning.
